This error comes from Spring Cloud Config Client (Spring Boot 2.4+) when your app expects an external config server but it’s not properly configured
.


From Spring Boot 2.4 onward, config loading mechanism changed.
If you include Spring Cloud Config dependency, Spring expects this property:
spring.config.import=configserver:


How to fix (3 options)
✔️ Option 1: You ARE using Config Server (recommended for microservices)
Add this in application.properties or application.yml:
application.properties
spring.config.import=configserver:
spring.cloud.config.uri=http://localhost:8888
application.yml
spring:
  config:
    import: configserver:
  cloud:
    config:
      uri: http://localhost:8888

Option 2: Config Server is optional
If your app should still run even if config server is down:
spring.config.import=optional:configserver:
👉 Best for:
Local development
Non-critical config server usage
✔️ Option 3: You are NOT using Config Server
Then simply disable it:
spring.cloud.config.enabled=false
OR
spring.cloud.config.import-check.enabled=false


Scenario	What to do
Using Config Server	spring.config.import=configserver:
Optional usage	optional:configserver:
Not using it	Disable or remove dependency